text: Too pricey than you get.... $$$.... better look for discount on some occasion. a lot of attraction still on renovation. Too much queue better buy the vip. Can't bring outside  food... but the food inside nothing special. Better eat first on outside before enter. Don't miss the parade...

Fun place to spend time with the family. I love this place. Will come back on my next visit to Bandung. Food price is pretty reasonable considering that it is a theme park. My fave theme in the park is the magical wizarding world theme. I can't wait to go here again.

An indoor theme park that is quite fun in my opinion, the place was clean and staff were smiling and very generous of their smiles. But it's crowded during holidays, I'd suggest getting the "VIP Pass" ticket so you wouldn't need to wait long to play a ride. They too have performance shows so be sure to check their show schedules near the escalator or entrance! Oh and there's a mini aquarium too inside.

Very nice indoor play. Seems its exactly same lay out to the one which is located in Makassar city. Bit hot thou inside.. probably not enough aircons.. even though today it's a weekday, can't imagine what gonna happen in crowded days

Visit the place for a robotic event. The place was crowded and full of school kids. Second time I come here nothings change. Still pretty the same. Please put your food and drinks in your bag and put it in the locker provided. It has thematic performance and change periodically. Food and beverages sell cashless use a card you can buy inside the park. Better come on weekday and if u are first timer ask for a map and remember the time for the carnaval.
Good place! You can see beatiful view and the fresh air there.
Very nice place yet cold. So prepare your thick enough jacket well.
I was there on a day of eruption 26 July 2019. It was terrifying but also beautiful indeed. I call myself lucky because i witnessed the one.

Was at Tangkuban Perahu recently but felt that it was a dormant volcanic crater awaiting to be erupted!!! However, the ride from Jakarta, up to the top volcanic mountain was exciting and very scenic. At the top, the pungent sulphuric or rotten egg smell could be overwhelming, occasionally. Beautiful from the top but could be scary at the bottom, near the crater.

An active volcano with a unique upside down boat shape, hence the the name Tangkuban (upside down) Perahu (boat) inferred. This gorgeous mountain is the most iconic landmark fills up the northside athmosphere of Bandung City. The surroundings are just perfect touristic areas making the small town called Lembang the most visited place especially during weekend and public holiday
Must see!
Wonderful creation by God. Sulfur smells is quite strong. Suggested not to stay for over 15minutes. Quite cold please bring a jacket over.
Well managed. Tickets are inexpensive. Very good views. Dont stay for one hour, you may only visit the crater for 30mins.

That sulfuric smell is like hell to unparalleled mind's view...
Lovely place!

Unique place, beware of high charge for car to park at the top, better park the car at the entrance and ride other transportation to top for cheaper entrance.
You need mask to be able to enter the crater site, so bring your own mask or you can buy overcharged mask at the top
Raised your hand if you like to spent time in a simple natural water fall even if you should go down stairs. See some sites and feel the sphere down there. Be happy breathing under the trees.
Raised your hand if you like to spent time in a simple natural water fall even if you should go down stairs. See some sites and feel the sphere down there. Be happy breathing under the trees.

My first visit was when I was 7yo. Been my favorite getaway spot ever since. Today I'm back after more than 30 years. The path towards been improved. The sound of the waters still ease up the soul. The breezes calms disturbed souls. But the water polluted way too bad along with poor view of garbages from upper hills mixed with the current. 
Thank God I'm not a foreigner that must be charged 55K for entrance. Domestic ones must pay 15K. Luckily, I've been here so many times, that I know so many entry-shortcuts, that I passed the retribution gate, only when I was exiting..
😉
Great place to escape to the forest and enjoy the famous waterfall Curug Dago. Near from the gas station and bus station.
Sooo beautifull water fall
Ticket price is 10-15k Rupiah and could also be use to enter other Great Forest Park Dago complex such as Tebing Keraton, etc.

A new Pasar Baru, located just the opposite of the old Pasar Baru. Even the name is same, Pasar Baru, but the old one is still maintain more crowded and full. I think, it because people already know that the Pasar Baru is over there. Or may be just because the old one is bigger and a lot of option to pick for every product.
got fever after come here. because alot people smoking in the building.. i never see any place where people can smoking freely in shopping complex building except here
Nice hotel in good location of shopping non stop. Rooms are big and clean. Breakfast good enough for filling the tummy before shopping and touring.
Shop for local goods such as kain sulam,kain batik, kemeja batik, laces all in one place. Building can be a little confusing. (-) smokers everywhere and beware of pickpockets

a great place to shop. bargain all you can. but be careful of pickpockets. be wary of your belongings and cash. they have everything from food to clothings to home appliances. huge market. allocated a lot of time to go here please. oh and if you have a local guide or friend, ask them to bargain for you. they will probably be able to get it cheaper than if you do it. but all and all, a great market to shop.

Nice, clean, cozy and well maintained guest house. 3 bedrooms with kingsize bed. Great place and suitable for family reunion with children (non smoking). Wi-Fi also available. Car park up to 4 cars (1 in garage, 3 in carport). Easy to find and noticed. Located near PVJ mall. Great hospitality as well. Recommended 👍👍

bersih, nyaman

It is a little hard to get to this place. The view is very beutiful but there are some trash here. The place is not very clean. I hope this lake will develop more because it's actually a very nice place.

It's a beautiful lake. Only should be careful while booking a boat as they just take you to a hotel inside and come back . Better to book individual boat and go for a boat ride if not interested in going to the restaurant area.

Thank you Situ Patenggang for giving the best for the world of tourism in Bandung, West Java.  All our international guests who visit Bandung, always ask to be invited to visit this place.  Because Situ Patenggang is famous for its beauty to the entire continent in the world.  And all our international guests have a good response to this Situ Patenggang destination.  Thank you Situ Patenggang.

This place is a quiet place when you visit it in weekdays.its a nice place for you to take children and enjoy the natural scenery. What impressed me was the place is very clean compare to another lake that I visited before, I don't know what strategy that the management of this place use, but I feel satisfy with what they do. The plants are well arranged they look fresh and tidy. I didn't see trashes either on the walking area nor on the water surface. I also feel glad of the boat men whose polite and explain their service politely. I would suggest this place for you to visit when you are in Bandung.
Visit this place with my family. Good view and recommended place to visit when you were in Bandung.
So nice and relaxing place . Natural hot water where you can take a nap with family and friends. The offer massage at a good price. Selling local food also
It's my second time.. With same company family gathering...  I love the food in here delicious and reasonable price.

I'm sorry, this is my first time to give a single star as a review. We were very disappointed of this place due to the service and ticketing payment. We were going in a group, then we entered to this place and asked the gate keeper. She said, once we bought the tickets, those would include everything, but the reality we must pay every single place we wanted to enter. That's not efficient and very expensive. Even for the toilet, really? We have to pay again? Oh come on! Nowadays many tour places give a great service with competitive price. It's not really recommended place to visit. Pay pay then pay again. Why not we pay at once kind of Ancol or Dufan. For example like Orchid Forest Cikole, that was very worthy to pay the price for that quality service they give. Thank you. I hope they can change the management for managing this wonderful place.
Strongly demand some private places for women so they can also enjoy the warm bath and foot massage (by a lady).
Water really hot here, they said its good for the joint since it has lots of sulfur
Great day with you

tempat ini sudah tutup permanen..
info dari warga sekitar sudah tutup hampir dua tahun..

Pertama kali kesini pas baru buka dan masih ramai pengunjung dan beberapa outboundnya juga masih banyak. Untuk tiket masuknya cukup mahal dan permainan yang bisa di mainin hanya 1 kali saja setiap jenis permainan.
Dulu punya kenangan disni, kepikiran mau kesini lagi, pas searching google maps udah tutup katanya :(
Udah tutup guys!

Lot of animals and birds. Some feel a bit weak but it’s not easy to maintain so many different species Together. Worth to visit especially with family and kids. Animals are friendly. Can get local food also inside nice in taste have some food stalls inside.

Bandung zoo at the present time is much more better than before. It is clean, offers you a great place to spend your time, fresh air, nice view, various healthy animals.. a fun way to learn about animals..

the zoo isnt being maintained well. the animals look starving. here's a picture of a bear that makes me sad when i saw it. i took a trip there with Rumah Harapan Indonesia for some vacation. i can see that the animals aren't happy. zoo is not that bad if they take care of the animals. even in the tiger's cage, there's only one of it, and really scared of human. its just sad to saw that

Place is easy to reach.

Dont expect it will have the same size or same quantity of animal collection as Ragunan in Jakarta. Its quite small and can be explored in 1-2 hours.

Its been improved significantly from before. Its quite clean and the pavement walk for the visitor is stroller friendly.

No big merchandise store.

I wrote new review because I saw so much improvement in less than a year (since August 2018) when I went to Bandung Zoo yesterday.

1. The renovation of the enclosures are still ongoing, BUT the staff didn't disturb the animals on the display so the animals aren't too annoyed with the presence of the humans.
2. Animals in the zoo look healthy. Mom played with her young, animal greeted the human, snakes are sleeping soundly in the cages that are fit for their size, crocs are sunbathing, the bears are playing with their cagemate, big cats are taking nap, birds walking around the aviary... So happy to see them yesterday.
3. The zoo is clean!!

Great job, Bandung Zoo!! Can't wait for my next visit there!!

Overall excellent outlet. Large parking spot. Various kinds of clothing. Very good selection of food stalls. There is a comfortable prayer room. In addition, the toilet is clean. I am not sure if the stuffs are genuine. The interior is really eye-pleasing with trees and koi.

Best factory outlet in town, very famous for Bandung citizens and foreign tourists as well. The clothes and goods are mostly (if not all), branded with discounted price. Best style and always updated. For the gentlemen waiting for the ladies to shop, the food court here is superb. There are a lot of clothing for gentlemen too. Did I mention the food court is superb? It also has a separated bags-only shop and souvenir shop. Expect fully crowded place when it's holiday season or weekends.

The place was quite big
From food to fashion
The item is somehow fake or rejected original.
The fake one was having a super quality.
The price was affordable.
The staff was good.
The place also was good.
You have many option to choose here.
Just prepare your money. 😐

Nice collection of colonial buildings that housed shops full of clothes, shoes, accessories, bags. Variety is decent but not terribly a lot, mostly t-shirts. The collections of bags and shoes are old although you could still pick out one or two quirky items that is still new. There is also a decent outlet of local cakes, confectionery and snacks where you can pick out a few choice ones to bring home to colleagues and friends. Reasonably priced and you might still find some good discounted items that are worth the price.
One of the most visited fashion houses in Bandung. Mostly local produced fashion with wide variety to choose from. The cafe and food corner offers snacks and many local street food, cheap and good.

Despite being one of the most traditional forms of art and music in Indonesia, Saung Angklung Udjo has never stopped improving themselves. They keep the audience engaged, making sure that no matter language you speak, you'd get to embrace the performances and appreciate the cultural values. No matter your age, you'd feel like a child again, finding out new wonders of the world. Highly recommended!

Best experience I had in Bandung. The emcee was really good, and the "conductor" who conducted the crowd Angklung playing really controlled the crowd. I had so much fun playing the Angklung, and the crowd was delighted every time we recognized the songs we were playing, AS we were playing them. Fantastic effort by the Udjo team!

Here is a place run by a family, keeping up the local traditions in music and dance. From children to adults were involved in the show. Mr Udjo even got the whole audience involved by teaching us to play the angklung. I very highly recommend people to visit this place.  The seating is very basic and can be uncomfortable for people with back problems to sit for the whole show which takes about 2 hrs. Making reservations ahead of time is not really possible but not necessary unless during peak season, I guess. A big applause to the host of the show, she was very clear and very good . The bands were excellent. The puppet show could be improved and maybe with a small movable stage, come closer to the audience. The children danced beautifully with charming smiles. Wish you all the very best!!

If u like music, u cannot miss this. "Angklung" is a musical instrument made out entirely of bamboo. You play it simply by shaking it. The music is very lively and capable to play a wide repertoire of music. There are 2 performances each day. U get a chance not only to listen, but play the instrument in a group!

The best resource for Angklung Music in one place. You can see live performance, see how it is made from barely bamboo tree to the ready instrument. Experience yourself how Angklung ensemble can be played by even an  inexperienced person and those who do not know  how to read musical notation.

This place can actually be amazing if they maintain their facilities properly. Some of the electronic/visual display is either broken or inactive. 

One of the display is under revitalization, so I was just visit at the wrong time. Toilet is clean and lighting is okay. I hope they create more interesting display as children will be fascinated with interactive shows.

Stone cutting workshop at the souvenir shop is used as a storage. Although the shirt souvenirs are actually really have cool design. 

Other than what I mention, the place is really nice and clean. It could use more staff to guide the visitors and larger space to show.

The museum was so good with a cheap prize! This museum tough me to be more concern about earth materials and earthquake. I love this place, but i don't think i will visit it for second time. The earthquake simulation was broken too. I hope the museum maintenance will be good next time.
This museum is great! It's very big and so modern. The earthquake simulator is also neat! I was there once and I am able to go to the warehouse. The warehouse is so great there are lots of fossils.

Nice small museum in heart of Bandung city. 
Not really big but it could encourage younger children to study earth science.

Small gift shop is available too, and it merchandise is quite good and come with reasonable price tag

Well-maintained and attractive, cheap entrance fees, but the parking lot is quite far from the museum.  I hope the collection continues to grow and props are constantly updated so this museum will be more interesting and we can learn a lot.

Lots variety of food from Indonesian food until Western and Japanese food..many of them offered cashback if you pay it with some electronic money such as ovo, gopay, danaku etc..open from 10 a.m and you can choose indoor or outdoor area..
It's nice place to eat and talk

A lot of food varities to choose from.
Prices are reasonable/competative.

Just looking for space to park your vehicle is horribly kayoes.

Avoid to come during Saturday & Sunday afternoon, or else you may not have any place to park.
If you still prefer to come among these days - better to come before lunch-time.

Aside of the Food Market, the hypermall is just few meters away to visit or to stroll with.
Cozzy place to hang out with family or colleagues
Cozy dining place
Beautiful scenery and fresh air
Nice view

Beautiful place... Pure nature... Just opposite to Kawa Putih volcano... Hot springs pool water is too dirty.... A small lake for boating.. Restaurant food very delicious and reasonable price... Overall a nice place to relax with family.
Polite & friendly service, one star lack because the garden is for production and not really beatiful for tourism
The stroberry are so fresh

One of the best mall. So tidy.. So clean.. All just great. We love to come here because the parking area that easy to access and all prices are good value. Five stars aren't enough.. More more. Best yet to come

Living in Bandung for almost two months but I just visited this place in a moment! It feels great! I like the concept very much. It looks modern and nature friendly. The first time coming here, I feel comfy. I feel like not going to the mall, but feel like coming to the nature with many shops. Recommended place to go hanging out with your friends!

Its definitely a different vibe compared to most shopping centres in Jakarta. A lot more open spaces and fresh air.

A must go to place whenever you were in Bandung. I love the recent changes in the city.

Interesting shopping concept. The Ciwalk was a market on a bridge but on a Sunday evening, it seemed quiet and most of the Indonesian tourists were in the mall next door. On the road level, there were many shops selling jeans and other things. A walk through is interesting but unless you want to shop, you don't need more than half an hour there.

Good and fun place to visit with family, friends or anyone you wanna with. Provide good atmosphere, semi natural environment with a touch of modern. Looks like this mall supports a Go Green concept.
Lots of food stations to visit and have a time to taste incredible dishes. 
You won't be lost in here. Only 2 floors and have a fun time here! 
Walking from the street you can find directly Burger King and D'Crepes as first bite of this place. 

Have a fun time!

Must visit place in Bandung, when you are looking for authenticity. Old place, but clean and tidy. I appreciate the guidance who take care of this place that become well maintained. Free entry ticket, allowed to take photos but not for videos. It will be more valuable if you get tour guide, that can explain you the history.

This Museum is awesome, even the place is just small building. But you can learn a lot about Asia Africa Conference history. This place is free, but they have "a break time" in 12 pm - 1 pm, so don't come around this time because they will ask you to leave the building in that time.

A worth to visit museum, especially for generation who was born at the end of the 1990-2000 era. This museum will provided you with documentation of the Asia-Africa Nation Conference held in Bandung 18-24 April 1955. 

During my visit there were some parts of the Museum being renovated, so generally the Museum can be divided to 4 parts.

1. Main Entrance. Enter from Asia-Africa Street, you will directly enter the Main Display Hall. It will provided you with documentation from the conference in form of news article copies, photos, voice recording, computer based informational database, to go out go to the north right corner
2. The Hallway. In this short hallway their will be billboards explaining Indonesian roles in worldwide politics nowadays.
3. The Assembly Hall. The original assembly hall used during the Conference.
4. Exit Room + Souvenir Store.

I got se many resourceful information about world efforts of peace building. There also some things left from 55 years ago, like sofa and chair. The tour guide is very friendly even for foreign tourist.

One of the places that you have to visit while in Bandung. Great place to learn about one piece of important history of Bandung. The place provides good lighting and air conditioning, very convenient for visitors. Tour guides are provided if you're too lazy to read the information yourself. Free entry for visitors. You need to consider using a taxi/going on foot because it's rather difficult to find a parking spot.
Good place especially for education about history of West Java. Toilet very dirty and the smeel are stinky. The persons of duty are not kindly. No attention.
One of museum where you can come and see historic about west java. Interesting knowledge.

One of the popular museum in Bandung. It shares mostly Sundanese culture and West Java history from stone age, middle age until now. This museum is well manage seen from its tidy appearance. Ticket cost around 3000-5000 idr
The Great Historical Refferences place in Bandung
Nice place. Clrar vieuw of Bandungs history.

Probably the kid’s best educational park in the country. It’s huge, it’s green, it’s clean, it’s educative, it’s well-maintained, it’s fun.

They got PG, and kindergarten school within the park. They also has swimming pool for kids.

The material displayed are very good.

One of my favorite place to visit in Bandung. I used to come here with my parents. Now I take my children here. It's a good place to visit with children. Your children can learn about road safety signs while playing. This place have mini-bikes and mini-cars to rent, a mini-train to look a round the park, a swimming pool, and spacious area for picnic or just strolling around.

It's been a while since my last visit. Actually it was almost 20 years ago. The place changed quite a lot, but the fun atmosphere is not gone. Kids still can rent bike to roam freely in the traffic track and my memories brought me back of how much fun I had in this place..and now my kids were having fun too..so it's cool. The park was quite clean and managed. Would be awesome if the small pools had full, clean running water resembling lakes in the middle of a forest. But overall it gave good experience for families with small kids. Learning about traffic, whilst chilling in a lush garden forest, in the middle of the city..

I love this place, it's cheap, but very nice. My daughter really enjoys playing here. Some of the things, like the slides need to be fixed, because they're a little dangerous and dirty. But overall, just a nice place to chill with your 3 year olds.

Great place which hold dearest memory from my earliest stage of life. Revisiting this place is therapeutic and strolling around the park always creates nostalgic atmosphere which take me back to my past. Unfortunately the downside is that there are many poorly maintained children playground which has many crack and hole that make it dangerous for kids to play around recklessly.

Mini waterfall but still nice. There are also provide archery, shooter games, hotspring indoor and outdoor, mini zoo.

View nya bagus, banyak tempat makan yg murah dan enak

Taman Bunga Cihideung Bandung buka setiap hari pada pukul 08.00 – 17.00 WIB. Jadi anda bisa datang setiap hari pada jam tersebut. Jika anda ingin berkunjung, sebaiknya anda datang pada pagi hari saat udara masih sejuk dan anda bisa menikmati wisata Taman Bunga Cihideung Bandung ini lebih lama. Bagi anda yang ingin berkunjung, anda dikenakan tarif/tiket masuk sebesar Rp. 5.000/ orang.
Sejak dahulu hingga saat ini, kita ketahui bahwa Bandung memiliki julukan sebagai Kota Kembang, kenapa? Ini disebabkan karena memang pada zaman dahulu di Bandung banyak tumbuh-tumbuhan yang tumbuh subur dan bunga-bunga cantik yang mekar memanjakan mata, sehingga Bandung pantas dijuluki sebagai Kota Kembang yang penuh keromantisan. Taman bunga memang mampu memberikan suasana yang berbeda dan dapat membuat hati merasa nyaman dan tenang. Terlebih lagi jika taman bunga ditata dengan rapi dan terdapat berbagai macam bunga yang indah. Memanjakan mata dengan jajaran warna-warni alami bunga dan menikmati aroma bunga yang segar serta suasana yang sejuk. Berbicara mengenai tempat wisata yang indah, terdapat sebuah desa di Bandung bagian utara tepatnya di daerah Lembang, Bandung yang masyarakatnya membudidayakan berbagai jenis tanaman hias berupa bunga yang sangat cantik dan cocok untuk dijadikan oleh-oleh oleh anda saat berkunjung ke Lembang. Daerah ini juga menyuguhkan pemandangan bunga tanaman hias yang cantik, indah, dan romantis di setiap pekarangan rumah warga, daerah tersebut bernama Taman Bunga Cihideung Lembang Bandung.
Tempatnya nyaman, enak untuk jalan-jalan sembari melihat tanaman/ bunga yang dijual
Harga bunga relatif murah... Pemandanga nya juga tidak buruk...
Cantik binti geulis
Tempat mencari bibit bunga
If you have kids, there is many play ground here and  they will enjoy.
Such a wonderful place to spend time with young kids. Lots of fun activities and lovely moments being close to nature and horses. Tasty and inexpensive treats are available. The staffs are friendly.

A Place Where You Be Cowboy & Cowgirl. The Ranch Has Amazing Western Atmoshpere. Nice Place To Bring Kids, Families & Friends.
They Even Rent Cowboy Suits Complete Package. I Bet Tthey Will Enjoy It So Much. Located In The Middle Of Lembang And Near Tangkuban Perahu
Kids love this place.. they have so many great activities for children. The weather and the view is also nice...worth every penny
Cool kids activities here! Its more fun than just playing or giving your kids a phone. More valuable and family time .. you will never forget and kids will excited!!

Firstly we will talk about the entrance ticket which is quite affordable, in my case 25k idr /person in the weekend and you can get a free drink (using an entrance ticket) don't worry about the parking area is very large, so you can come here anytime. Secondly I enjoy the air here, it's so fresh. I really like the atmosphere in here. The views is really nice. There are a lots of places you can enter to take a good picture, spending time and enjoy everything, of course with separate payments. If you have children this is a best place for them, so many activities and education for them to choose and play from land to water. Thirdly food court near the lake and so much food that you can buy whatever you want. The food is delicious, prices range from 10k to 30k. No cash transactions at this place so you have to exchange into a coin that we can buy at the entrance or at some point to buy things and no refunds.

Amazing place for kids as this is more a kids and family amusement park.

If you come for a floating market.. that’s not what I expected it to be. There are small boats at the dock where you can buy food, that’s it.

 Beautiful garden as well.

If you are looking for activity with kids, this is a 5 star place. If you want to go for a floating market.. this is not going to be completely satisfying.

Great place to bring your kids here. They'll love to play, walking around, and enjoy the scenery. Kids will enjoy role playing, feeding rabbits, flying fox, look around the mini train, mini city. Foods also good with reasonable price. Don't forget to change your ticket with drinks at the booths inside.

There was very little floating-market-action. Was more of sight-seeing than anything, and I must admit - the garden and the Japanese area were really nice and well-maintained. Only got here so I could get to the Rainbow Garden, but it was somewhat more than I expected in the end.

Great Recreational Facility for the family. Priced reasonably well. Great fun for the kids at the KOTA MINI and the FLOATING MARKET. Variety of fun and colourful activities for the kids. Even some for adults. Parking is great and some are from buses. Many great delicacies are available, coffees are very general, but the juices are fresh and made to serve.
Nice place 👍, very good to takes pictures, fresh air,natural
Beautiful tea plantation.. Just need park your vehicle near plantation and just walk here. It's better if the weather was good. Be careful maybe you will find caterpilar :D
Such a great place and lovely view of tea plantation on south Bandung
Beautiful view! This place is very relaxing.
Good landscape  to see.. only pay for parking ticket  around 2000-5000 rp..

It's so happy walking around here
The air very fresh and the ticket so cheap absolutely (Rp 2000/people)
You can buy additional ticket for great experiences in special guest room (you can rent only Rp 10.000/people for 20 minutes)

Could be worse for the same price. There's so many people because it was during holiday season. The water became less hot and more dirty quickly. It's better to get there early to have the best experience as the place is getting more crowded during the day. It opens at 7 am. The ticket include free pool area. Also  there's a little less crowd pool for 10k rupiah, 20k/30min for private bath and 150k/hr for private family pool.
The shower area is pretty open, you better shower with friends to cover you during your shower.
Great place with great view of mountain from pool. So crowded during holiday.
Nice route to come here, many good place for family..
This place sucks. The ticket paid didn't include the hotspring. The pool was bad. Not recommended.
Recommended for family trip! Also for camping, playground, nature refreshing, and outbond. Entrance tickets are affordable.
Lovely place! Must visit especially if you are visiting The White Crater.
A great camping ground for family and friends gathering. Try not to come on weekend or national holiday because it will be very crowded.
Amazing scenery. I'd recommend going early in the morning as it would get crowded. Especially in the weekends.

Blend with nature at Ranca Upas Bandung West Java,thank you ranca upas for giving the best for Indonesian tourism, all of our international guests if visiting bandung, always visit this beautiful place.

It's quite small yet beautiful. Love it so much. Hope the flowers will be more various next time.

Anyway, I know a girl name Nadya there. She is very smart and kind. Hope she will be success in the future. Good luck, girl!

To be honest,this place is not that great. Just a small garden with some flower in it. At first i thought it was great. But as soon you get in. You just amaze for a very short period. When i came there the rabbits are sick and they told me the animal are fine. But they are really not fine. They are sick and need to be cured. Oh and this place had a very small parking spot for motorcycle.
Good value for money. Nice view to see. Good landscape decoration.
Beautiful setting of flowers in the garden. You can also buy both decorative  plants and vegetables. Have to prepare umbrella or sunhat as it is an open space.
Its a great place to take place. The price is not expensive either, but you have to pay 50 K extra if you're using a professional camera

We as a family had a great time spending the night in the tent..great activities and games for kids, and the place is beautiful..the pine forest atmosphere is present throughout the place from the entrance, to the hiking track we walk through in the morning. Be sure you're in time for roasted corn and bonfire at night (included with our stay) and morning walk through the forest..the air is quite cold, especially at night..so be prepared.. we recommend to bring your own blanket or sleeping bags for sanitary reasons. Friendly staffs, and the great thing is, it is not so far away from convenience stores and restaurants..will be staying here again, maybe we'll try the premium tent next time..thank you grafika

Good place to camp, surronded by forest, but easy to reach main street. You also can find some cottages to sleep over with your family. There are many good place to visit near this place, such as Tangkuban Parahu Volcano, Floating Market, The Ranch and many more

Great place. Big park in this area with many attractions like flying fox, hanging bridge, tree house, etc. Also there is a coffee shop and restaurant inside the park. Lots of menu, delicious foods, affordable price. Recommended.

Good place for relaxing to get fresh air and back to nature. With entrance fee IDR 15.000 for explore the area by our self not to bad. My suggestion for entrance ticket is better can to change for drink. The location Grafika Cikole is in lembang, Bandung.
Nice place, well-arranged and has good spots for camping. Make sure you don't forget to wear warm clothes because it's really cold here, especially at night.
The road is a little bit challenging, but the view and ambience is really great. Nice place and friendly staffs. We hope the owner can continue improving the facilities.
fresh air...nice place

It was great. I came when it was raining and thought nobody was there when i arrived. Went up a bit and many people sat outside and was singing and drinking coffee (lokals) then they said i could stay with them in the house and the owner was really nice giving food and all. :)
Beautiful location right beside great hiking trails. The staff were incredibly nice and helpful too.
Wonderful place for group camping but need extra efforts to get there

Very good place to hang around with friend and family. A trip which will be always stays as a memory in your photos..You can click your memorable photos over here. There are experts as well to click your photos and they will charge a nominal amount for the same. You will also get a welcome drink which is included in the entrance ticket.The place entrance usually closes at 5pm indonesian time.Beautiful place great adventure..

Went for the camping experience and loved it a LOT! Coziest camping ever, the tent is big and the beds are super comfortable. Shower is a bit challenging on the shared bathroom and not enough hot water but other than that it's all great. Food was good, especially for breakfast and I really enjoyed the guided hiking trip through the pine forest. The staffs are all super friendly and helpful.
The ticketing service is very slow. Redemption of food is also very slow. The view was nice but the slow services turned off my mood.

If you like to go to this place, you need to have one day tour because there are some interesting attraction that you can try.. Tips for coming here: coming early, bring umbrella, use pants (casual) and do not wear skirt or dress if you want to play here.. all the ticket attraction is around 20k-25k.. and if you want copy of your photos, they charge 10k per pic and will send to your mobile phone

This was a nice visit. I think you would need a car rental or arrange your travel here since there's no public transport run to the lodge. The route was pretty nice because it's honestly going to the uphill of Bandung area. For each section, you'll need to pay separately with the entrance ticket. They're pretty affordable. The view was nice too but it can get really crowded during weekend.
Nice place, very well managed and clean. Buy feeds to feed animals like calf, rabbits, sheep. There is even a lizard and rabbit petting station for up-close encounter with animals.
Nice place for strolling around here at Lembang. But so crowd with a lokal tourist.

author_name: Mohammad Zaki Amani Bin Abd Rashid
text: Very good.. comfortable.. you can bring your family
Very nice place to visit. Good for kids to interact with sheeps and rabbits
it's a very good place to bring you family for recreation & education

Really nice place, love it. Has good facilities and snacks. My siblings ride the glamping trike ( i don't know what to called that) and they said it rock!! The scenery is absolutely beautiful, although the access road in the area is still rough. Overall I'd come back here in my next visit to Bandung.
Very beautiful camping site! Staff was very friendly, I only recommend maybe adding more activities at the camp site itself.
It has a great restourant with unique shape of building. The restourant just look likes a big ship
Perhaps on weekdays the place would offer true serenity. Otherwise , weekends are madness
Place really nice... but.. parking lot its awful... its gravely.. ruin ur tires... fix em please...

This camping ground should he called the Amazing Spots For Instagram because what all you can see here is all instagramable spot. We cant help taking pictures here especially for the background of Tangkuban Perahu. It looks like a paint that has been drawn by the God. Now, this place has been very famous, all young people spend their weekend here to enjoy the milky way and cold weather in the night
Ok
Awesome

Cocok bwt camping atau cross country. Danaunya tdk terlalu tinggi.. Udaranya sejuk hingga ke tulang ^^
Ada tempat khusus utk berfoto, view nya bagus.. Pengunungan dan hutan

Tempat wisata alam alternatif di daerah Bandung Barat dengan pesona keindahan hutan pinus. Air terjunnya tidak begitu bagus. Banyak objek untuk membuat foto yang intagramable.

Jalan menuju ke tempat ini masih jelek, sangat berbatu.

Curug Tilu Leuwi Opat is located around Ciwangun Indah Camp, Parompong, Bandung Barat. To get the waterfall "Curug" from the parking lot, we're going into the woods and we  have to walk down the river. We're about to cross some exotic wooden bridges. It'll take about one hours leisurely pace. fresh air and green view inside the forest.
Good place for hiking... all your hardwork pays off

Nature escape. Walking down rocky path, a bit slippery, walk through watergate , few modestly bridge, we didn't reach the third waterfall only two because the path a bit more slippery and steep. Just be more carefull. I go with 5 children age 10 to 14, they can manage it. You can't swim at the second waterfall because the flow is too strong means dangerous. I hope Perum Perhutani willing to give more attention to this kind of places especially giving safety path. Some bridge need to be fix. There's also camping ground & outbond activities. Pay 10 thousand rupiah for entry per person & 5 thousand car park.
This is a quiet place that you can have a relaxation here
Beautiful scenery and not many person know it yet

Located Center Of Lembang. Near Tangkuban Perahu And Many Lodges.
The Air So Fresh And Cool. Jendela Alam Offers Alot Of Amusement Playgrounds. Bring Your Children & Friends. They Will Have Fun Together

A farming edutainment center at lembang highlands. Excellent for family with many children activities. You can buy its farming products such as eggs and vegetables. The surprising thing is its very clean. It also accept group travel from schools and other institution. A really must visit when you travel to
Bandung.
Great place for kis educations, but over price for additions pack and swimming pool must be maintenance
Greeny+like in the zoo.... 🌳🌿🐴🐰😍😻
Edutainment place for kids. Cool!

Ciwangun:
This place is greatly amazing for adventure lovers! Road in here quite tough and need stamina also endurance if you want to get more fun experience in here. Usually, scouting program use this place, or church retreat program, leadership training and many more. Tea garden is one of the iconic spots in here to do many activities in groups. 

Especially in the morning and evening are good times to take pictures in here. The air is very fresh and free from beasts. Be mindful of your belonging and if you bring kids, because this place is quite mountainous and has narrow cliff. This place quite accessible for car, bus or motorcycle. There are shops near the exit gate for buying some merchandise.

I recommend the management team in here to put signs to warn the visitors. Rope with sticks also to provide a line sight especially during the night. More places to sit like gazebo or bench. Bring sticks if you need to walk through mountainous area. The price is quite affordable especially for in groups of people.

 The facilities in here quite good, just keep up the cleanliness. Overall, this place is very recommended for those of you who wants a vacation with nature theme.

Good place to relax with big family, just expect less on the food! it was acceptable, however can be better with the price paid. 
Think they precooked the fishes as it was warm [not freshly hot].

If you want to do fishing, they sell the fishing stick at IDR8k and IDR12k for the bait.
They also charge minimum of IDR55k [1kg] if you managed to catch fish! 
If it's less than 1kg they will top up the fish for you.
Don't forget to visit the tea plantation on top. Reaaly nice view. The entry fee is cheap. Road access to the camp is bad.. specially after the rain.
The acces road was  in bad condition. The panoramic as usually, not too attractive.
Unique place to visit, easy to reach, alot of good spot for taking pictures, but is is not like you will saya "Wow!!" when you get there
You should pay 20k to entrance this site. If you enjoy the train you would like it but if it's not dont go to this site
My son loves this place! We're hoping they continue to maintain this place better.
We had a good time here. My children love to see the mini town with train miniature here, they felt like they were ultraman. You should pay Rp20k for entrance fee.

405/5000
Our daughter loves to play in the miniature railway park, see the train running, see the mini-detail set. Ask about the new thing he saw. As a place of education, this miniature park is perfect for children in order to increase insight, increase the power of imagination. The location is classified as cool, it helps to make children feel at home and linger in this place.
My kiddo's favourite place. Been here many times. Always exciting to get back here. A good place to bring your kids if they love trains, beside the real train station of course... hahaha
Nice to enjoy with friends and family, no need to pay entrance fee. Lote of things to see large panorama. Many place to enjoy food and coffee. The food not expensive

Recommended spot for taking pictures with panoramic view. Peak hour in the afternoon, entrance fee 15K / person in return you'll received a voucher with the same value. The voucher can be redeem only for soft drinks, bakery, crackers and ice cream (Can be accumulated). Foods value area variable, food ordered system are like Solaria restaurant.

This is the first area I get into, and I didn't know we have to buy tickets to enter. I'm really sorry. I was just following some people going downstairs (beside the cafe) and apparently, it was not the entrance. Surprisingly, no one tried to stop us? They were just giving us a look but without explanation, of course I wouldn't know. Honest. I recommend to put a sign on the stairs that lead directly to the backyard.

Romantic, comfy, cool place for hangout with great ambiance. It doesn't matter you come in day or night, if you come in day you got the Bandung view, if you come in night you got the romantic ambiance. Personnally i prefer to come for dinner. They have a private room (more like a tent) so you cant be bothered by other guess. Its perfect if you want to propose or tell you feelings towards your girl.
Food ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Place ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Price ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Service & Hospitality ⭐⭐⭐⭐

Marvelous place to visit, with Bandung City view at night, many good photo spot. 

The food is good, staff are friendly, but took a while waiting your food. 

Large parking space, but narrow road to reach this place. 

A must visit place during your time in Bandung.

After walking for about one Km from the entrance post, you will meet a 3 prong Cross road. I hear that from the left, the first load leads to a trail through a village, second leads to tangkuban Perahu (volcano mountain that just erupted) and the 3rd path leads us up to the view point of putri then path loops back to the entrance. Wished I had time to do all 3 trails but took the 3rd one instead. 
We went hiking in late morning weekday and its super quiet. Nice and quaint.
Love the pine tree forest. Paths are super sandy it coated my hiking shoes orange brown. 
Took just 30min to slowly walk up to the beautiful view point. Air was so cooling and view was therapeutic. Coming down was only 20min slow walk. Totalling up to only 2.5km.
Thus the trail is easy but wears shoes with good grip because the path is sandy and can be slippery if your running shoes have poor grip.
See the pictures for the journey up.

Note: this is not the peak of the cliff but only a midway point up to the moutain.

Putri moutain was beautifully stunning though
Cozy camping ground with such fresh air.
It's the top of the mountain. Don't you think it's beautiful?
This place is really good for a casual camping, and there's a historical site too. There's also a nice view of lembang from above. The ticket isn't expensive, and the environments are quite clean.
Buat hiking sangat cocok, mau pagi mau sore pemandangannya bagus... Dari sini bisa terlihat farmhouse dari sisi berbeda
Mantap asli ' cuma akses jalan agak jauh masuk lg ke perkampungan tapi bagus blm banyak pengunjung masih perawan lah camping juga bisa kayanya..
Pemandangan nya moi, sayang banyak bagian sudah menjadi milik pribadi, walau masih bisa utk melintas saja

Expredisi malam di jalur bukit panjebolan , ternyata memang mencengangkan hehe tapi seru kalo banyakan kesini , tetapi ketika siang hari bagus indah bisa lihat kota bandung dan lembang , melihat wisata fame  house dari atas bukit , melihat bukit bintang dari kejahuan .

Enak buat camping , hiking atau motoran sambil camping , namun di tempat ini tidak ada wc dan warung 

Jalur nya cuman di lewatin untuk motor , jalan bebatuan kerikil aspal ancur ,tanaman yang lebat mungkin sudah bertahun tahun tidak ada lagi yang melewati jalur itu karna memang sepi banget
Ini adalah salah satu tempat untuk berkumpul bersama teman teman seperti camping atau hiking

This is probably the best lesser known spot in Bandung. I was here as part of the South Bandung motorcycle tour. The parking location was at an unassuming spot. You can either walk to the location (15 minute short hike) or take an ojek (10K rupiah). When I visited, there was no charge to the place! You can take a 5 minute short walk around the crater to see the fumaroles and boiling pool.

The hot springs feels clean and there are not many people there - mostly locals. I also like how they smartly make pipes where you can drench yourself in hot water. There is a toilet there for you to change. No lockers around, but you can put your things in the hut.

Amazing, lovely made hot Pools with very friendly and kind locals. Thank you for letting us take part of your wonderful nature Spa. To all tourists, please keep the place clean and treat the locals with respekt.
Kawah yang unik dg kolam berbentuk love dan bisa mandi lumpur
Lumayan bagus tp kebersihannya harus di tingkatkan
Tempat nyah masih nyaman..
Nice hike. The water is shallow though
It's something!
natural

Ane seh k sini pake sepedah, jd ga nyusurin sungai tp naik k atas lewat perkebunan teh Cipanji. Pas ada gedung terakhir... hutan deh kesananya. Nyusurin hutannya ga sampe 1,5 km setelah itu ada per3an/ jalan cagak, ambil yg ke kiri... jalan setapak sekitaaaarrr... 300 m an Bisa d bil nyusurin lereng. Tar jalan setapak abis, br deh "terjun bebas" ke kebun ga keurus sekitar 100 m an. Br ketemu curug kecilnya. Untuk k curug Cipanjinya, harus nyusurin sungai k atas sekitar 50 m
Indah, mantap, suasana nya sejuk, alias dingin buanget kaya masuk ke air kulkas,😂😁😀😊
Nice place

Are you looking for natural attractions in Bandung? like the waterfall? just visit the ciwidey curug tilu waterfall. The view along the road to the place is very beautiful because along the way you will see a very large tea garden. Besides the nice scenery, the air is cool. Entrance ticket to Curug Tilu is very cheap. There the atmosphere is very cool, peaceful and quiet. For those of you who love fishing, there is a fishing place available and you can immediately burn the fish there. This place is perfect for vacationing with family. Besides there are 3 waterfalls, there is also a very nice view and of course instagrameble. So for those of you who like nature tourism, just visit Curug Tilu Ciwidey
Wonderful.. Small but great
Wonderful !
Fresh

Small place, the mushroom shaped trees garden is only about 200m long. 

The road access is terrible.

What saves the day is the beautiful green carpet look of tea plantation garden.
Perfect place to take a rest and for honeymoon. Still natural and nice view from in the top of hills. Tea plantations so perfect. I love it

Quite far from main road and the road condition not smooth. The mushroom hill itself is quite good. Perfect non mainstream place to visit while in ciwidey. The scenery is excellent. Better to arrived here in the morning or at noon, so that you have enough time to go back before dark.
One of the most photogenic and insta-worthy place I have ever been yet the way me and my friends to get here was quite challanging. But It's worth a try. Sure I'd like to go back.
Lovely place
Great natural park for your kids, this place has waterboom for your kids. But doesnt have animal :(
Good place even though it is not too large.. But I was very happy.
The view is instagramable with a mountain background. There is also a swimming pool but unfortunately the water is cold. Road access is still inadequate especially for buses, to be careful
It's quite far from the main street. Mainly it's a water park, but they provide many photo spot.
A great for short trip ....and not too far up ..

Camping ground, penangkaran rusa, tempat yg cocok untuk mengadakan acara trail

Awesome... natural ....fresh.... and amazing place...
Good place to camp and feel the sound of earth ... thos place is excellent...

When we were here, the pool was in the middle of cleaning and the water weren't filled yet. The only accessible pool was the children one but its not warm or even hot enough. We were also bothered by the locals who persistently offering us to buy their strawberry even when we already said no. The pool & area around it also look quite dirty.
But the scenery in here was so amazingly beautiful. You can enjoy the pool view with the mountains & hills surrounding you and the sound of the forest nearby were so mesmerizing.
The rate is not associated with its hotel becauaw we only stop for the kids who wants to play on their outdoor playground...

So old and low maintenance

A lovely place, a lot to explore. And if you're an mountain bikers you can enjoy the view and the fresh air while riding some cool trails, but you need to know where they are since theres no sign for the trails.
Best Place to see Sunrise
Beautiful place with clean and fresh air
hiking biking ngibing ... ti'is

It is a 100 metre waterfall easy surrounded by greenery and fresh air. The climb down is by stairs and well maintained considering other national Parks we visited. This is a wonderful waterfall with many a view points as you descend downwards. There is a pool for taking dip in the fresh water. It is better than nearby man-made floating market or glamping areas.
Good scenery, easy access but you must have strong legs. This place have a lot of stairs. And be careful with wild macaca

Your typical Curug (mini waterfall, in Indonesian).
Still has that clean water for your Instagram feed, lots of monkeys (not as populated as monkey forest), but better put your snacks and accessories inside your bag.
NOT RECOMMENDED FOR ELDERS, and PEOPLE WITH KNEE PROBLEMS. It has long-long stairs, and some may find some parts of the way a bit slippery. 
The Curug itself is quite safe for teens (not kids) and young adults, and they have restrooms.
Love it so much... so relaxing and so peaceful. Would love to include this place again in my next Bandung visit

The air and water are so clean. You don't need air conditioner in this place. There are swimming pools and tourist attractions nearby. The rooms are cozy and neat. The water in the bathroom can be set to be hot/cold. Some of them are vroken though but, it's tolerable.
Be careful with people offering things you will get charge for it without any information.
Fresh air. I also using guide to get more information about this place
Nice short escape from hustle bustle of Bandung City
Nice place but the guide really persistant even after rejected make me annoyed lol
Wow.. Amazing.. So nature..

This is my home ..
Is very beauti 
And i love it
Good area for camping ground. The facilities are improved a while ago and i believe it still go on till now. Best for family / group vacation.
A beautiful view with nice park and clean river to visit
The road is not yet ready , but still awsome because the view, the air. The gazebo is dirty although there is trashes, i dont have any idea!
Love this places 🤩
make sure to bring your sweater. its cold up here. some view you can only see with your own eyes.
Best view actually  but really effort if you bring car. And u should pay 10k for car and 30k/ pax u can get meal and drink. Quite expensive actually. Better u stop at bukit moko than here.
Nice place for weekend esape.but half the road is damaged ( by car ). Need more attention from the government.
Nice place for camping..cold & fresh air..
Nice to chill because it is located at a high altitude. Provide camping ground too. Not too far from Central Bandung. Can be reached in 1 hours by car.

Sunrise place, take 50k to take motor ride up to the hill. Plus entrance ticket 55k for foreigner. Open at 5am but the guard might come late 5.20 plus. The view of cloud is amazing. Cold wind up there, need to prepare jacket. The sunrise ended about 7.30am.

Beautiful place and refreshing air. This place has adequate facilites such as road pathway and bathrooms. What needs to be fixed is the security and visitor's behaviour. Visitors often jump over the fences in order to take photos and that jeopardizes their safety.
come early at 5am and you will see beautiful sunrise from the top. cool place to get a pictures

The place is well managed. Pathways and stairs leading to the viewpoints are well built. Security (regarding visitors jumping over the fences) could be improved: i.e. right now no officials supervising visitor's behaviour.

Used to like it so much but lately become too crowded with too much tourist.
Need to start about 5 a.m in the morning to have best view of the cloud below. Jun-Aug is the best months to come.

Good place for couple, hangout with friend, or family. They have good restaurant, clean, fresh air, and great views. And you can ride boat here. They even have nice playground for kids. For you guys who like some nature or landscape photography this place is perfect for you.

It offers luxury and economic benefit in the same time. If you have money, you can enjoy facilities to the max, but if you have medium budget, you still can enjoy forest atmosphere and medium budget menus

Clean, well maintained, fresh air, friendly staffs and great view. Its around 1 hour from Bandung, but easy to reach by car. Bungalow and glamping site also available, but the prices are quite expensive. Suitable for family with kids. Most of all its recommended 👍

A beautiful bamboo village with nice scenery and cool fresh air. There are few spots to take some great pictures. Worth the hassle to travel from the city. It took me an hour plus to get here but do remember to use private renting car. Very hard to get transport back to city. And do try out the Burangrang restaurant simply delicious and affordable. The entrance fee is Rp30K.
Good place and nice surrounding. The temp below 20 deg C.. the food is expensive especially in the lake area.. its offer a glamour camping and cottage
Nice view but up to the hill and crowded in holiday

The great hotspring in wild. Very awesome 
I love this... Instagram: zhulfikris
Developing garden and water flow
Recommended place for vacations, with friends or Family
Good flying ground for children

Clean, with a beautiful architecture. You can find labyrinth park with large tree in the middle. There is also free drinkable tap water. Smoking is forbidden here so the air keep clear. For tourists who want to take bandros (cute little bus to take you around Bandung) you can buy the tickets here directly from the driver

didn't really go there, since it was just a pass by on my way to take Bandung City Tour Bus there.
But as long as i walked there, i found it a really beautiful and peacefull park in the middle of the city.
Lots of big trees and smoking prohibited area make the air there so fresh.
This place quietly clean, hopely it could stay as that forever.
Even lots of children playing and swimming in the fountain.
I wish i could move in to that city.

Clean place, often used for ceremony or certain event. The place is free to visit and expectedly safe because the security is in good amount to patrol all sector of the area. The place is also large enough to accommodate thousands of people if needed.
Very relaxing place to chill. You can do various activities and meet a lot of communities here
Great park! It is so wide, covered by trees. Nice lighting, and there is also some animals such as rabbit and goose. It's very comfortable place to enjoy.

Large, natural, landscape-shaped theme park.

Pros:
1. Natural surroundings. Pavements made easy for access.
2. Unique shaping that follows the nature. Great for vacation and sports.
3. Many features and facilities. One of the best place for large groups vacation.

Cons:
1. There should be sheltered easy walk path that connects to every directions. Which helps the elders, people with wheelchair, kids, and especially when downpour.
2. Guard rails, safety nets, and warning signs especially for dangerous stairways and steep edges are almost all seem missing here. Safety first! Never open before safety provided entirely.
3. Make more dedicated ticket booth for each feature. The park guys/clerks that scatter through the place to warn or help customers.

We visited on weekday, so all the park was for ourselves! It was great. We hated the system, though. Could we receive some kind of special card with deposit or something so we can just swipe it to enter other than trying to locate a ticket booth every single time we want to try a ride? That was tiring. Other than that, we loved the place.
Well developed, well managed, need more adrenaline junkies attraction. The flying fox too short and not so high. met the west java governor on opening day, yay.

Good place for young people and children. This place has many attractions such as archery, photo spots, etc but is a bit difficult to reach because of the hilly location. And you need to pay the ticket around 30k at each attraction. The ticket can be exchanged for souvernirs or ice cream.

Too many photo sites, decent options for activities available, not enough area to play for kids. 

Food stalls are just okay, cleanliness can be improved.

This is an awesome place to visit. This place is huge. For those who loves to take pictures you might need to spend at least 2 hours here. Very eye soothing place, peace and very comfortable. You will get a free ride of flying fox when you purchase the Wood bridge entrance tickets. I highly recommend. Very worth going.

Consider this a walk through a paid park in the midst of a pine forest. Foreign tourists pay 10K rupiah for admission. Not the most outstanding collection of orchids I've seen (but I'm from Singapore where Orchid is our national flower). The orchids are housed in a greenhouse in the "forest". Each species of rarer orchids is then in a display box of sort. This shld be the highlight of this Orchid Forest. Short of impressive personally. 
Through out the park there are multiple photo points. The park is decorated decently for those who love to take portrait style pictures around. 
Other than that you can try some adventure activities such as zip lining or crossing a wooden bridge. Just note every other activity is chargeable. 
There is a small rabbit enclosure where rabbits are roaming free range and you are able to play with them (non-chargeable). Carrots are available for a small price for feeding.

I went here because of some blogs' recommendation and I was happy I did! It was a lot better than my expectations. The garden design is really good and the view is amazing. I love the forest and I think I could stay here all day. It's good for a family hang out or a weekend trip. The place is pretty big, so although I came there during holiday, it wasn't too crowded.

So many attractions, so little time! The ambiance was lovely. The bean bags at the small 'restaurant' were comfy. The rabbits were cute (also like how they were allowed to run around the pen!). An abundance of nice photo-taking spots. I had a great time here.

It's always good to have a getaway from the crowded city of bandung. You can get here in 2hours by car. But mind you, the road was not easy and pretty but the scenery is worth it. You only need to pay 30k for entrance and inside the forest you can see glass House full of rare orchid, there's child playground and restaurants to fill your empty stomach.
Great Nature place. Worth the hike. Be prepared for a long and tedious hike through rocky terrains tho. Pretty harsh track if you are not used to hiking.

If you want to have the 3D effect on your picture, make sure you take the pictures from this spot. You need to take off the shoes to get around the room. This place is divided into some parts based on the theme. Outside the building, when I was there, there are some stalls selling food and drink. Nice for selfie
Bandung city view is breathtaking from here, if you also do hiking. You'd better off to the 2nd summit than the 1st one.

Great Bandung city view from Mt Manglayang's Shadow Peak. I bet the view would be amazing at night...

Trekking is best after rainy season. Very slippery.

There were 5 steep incline to reach the summit and another 2 steep decline to reach the Shadow Peak.

If you have trekked Mt Burangrang, the difficulty factor is twice, although its distance and elevation is less than Burangrang.

If you looking for "Hiking trail for beginners", then Manglayang is the right choice. 
It's summit is not too high, 1818 masl. 
But it has "a real hiking track" with all of those tree root climb, stone wall (not too high, approx 2 meters) and so on. 
Yet this real jungle experience is not that long to finish. With 2-3 hours slow walk, we can reach it's peak.

And it's just at the backyard of Bandung City.
Best track are from Batukuda Cileunyi. About 2.5km hiking trails. Just dont under estimate this mountain. 1818 MASL seems light but you'll know if you try yourself.
Easy to reach from Batu Kuda
A nice and fun way to walk through nature... It still feels nice even in the middle of the day.. Fun to bring kids along. But I think it could be better, hope to come here again often

Definitely one of the best designed galleries in Indonesia. The collections are intimately displayed and can be observed from a very close range. Nuarta's works are intriguing and contemplative, you can easily spend hours to observe the intricate and dramatic sculptures. The gallery was pretty much empty when we visited on Friday afternoon. It was good for us but left us wonder why not so many people were there. The ticket is very reasonably priced though and totally worthed the price.

It's such an experience, especially for those who can appreciate arts. The location itself is rather magical; peaceful and seemingly untouched, far from the maddening crowd. Totally worth the visit if you're looking for something different (and for sure, so many Instagramable spots, you'd be so satisfied)

Welcome to sculpture gallery of Nyoman Nu Art. In a wide places and surround by green hood that the creation stay, its a fine masterpiece and will be a good views for those who like to see or wanna join their art program too (its amount to few arts not only one activity). Just reach them through they info services for further info. Sometimes there is an art exhibition. You have to buy ticket for entering this gallery. Whether you feel exhausted after views the gallery then you could meet the resto. There are two parts of it.  One inside the sculpture building, the other is behind the prime build you can through some beautiful park till get there. Happy seeing those masterpiece!
Exceptional art and gallery, great ambience, fresh air and you can have a cup of coffee and eat bebek goreng ala bali. And if you are lucky, you can meet Bapak Nyoman Nuarta and Ibu Nyoman.

I believe Mr. Nyoman Nuarta is not only a talented artist but also a smart businessman. I'm amazed how succesful he is in a country who doesn't value art much. When I visited his art gallery, I didn't just see art pieces being displayed. But I saw... Life. The building is well designed and maintained. The park has beautiful plants and trees. The restaurant, Laxmi? OMG, I tried their ayam betutu and I swear it was the best ayam betutu I've had so far. Must try! I also went to the gallery shop but I couldn't find small merchandise like keychain, stickers, fridge magnet. Mostly they sell small businesses products which are quite pricey. Well I bought the catalog book though and I love the pictures. Anyway, I took some pictures at NuArt Sculpture Park and still amazed how beautiful Mr. Nyoman Nuarta's art work.

What an awesome experience we had. Stayed 4D3N and enjoyed every single moment of our stay. Their hospitality is beyond words, akin to a five star hotel. Strongly recommend if you need a getaway from the city life. Will definitely come back.

If you need to purchase snack or things the management provide stalls/stores at the basement level. You won't find any stalls on the surface or street level.

Usually at night there's a local Night Festive Market open on the empty field on the east side of the Square, just go across the East Side Street.

Worth-visiting place in Bandung, most visited with instagrammable surroundings. Dating back to 1920s you can see the magic of grand architecture in every details of the building. The Gedung Sate means Sate Building, inferred from a sate (Indonesian style yakitori, beef in skewer) structure right on top of the main tower. Just mention the name to any Bandung people, and all will point to the same unique building
Gedung Sate, the icon of West Java Province. Beside governmental office, you can also enjoy the museum tour there.Good place and I  recommend you to visit during your trip in Bandung
An interesting tourist spot. In the Gedung Sate  we can see colonial design, Bandung museum, enjoy the park, and relax in the coffee shop. The best time to enjoy Gedung Sate at 2 pm - 5pm.
iconic in bandung. very interested place

It's a place to watch and learn about science and basic technology. They have lots of experimental props which you can try to operate, discover or watch it. The place not to big, better guided, help to explain the instruction or explanation board to your children aged 3 to 9. You have to park at giant supermarket, there's a security guard will help you across the street.

This place has developed some of their booth, they added some new experiments and the kids love it. My 3 years old daughter was also able to enjoy some of the experiments especially the experiments which technical shows like the ball with different track and the marbels that go trought a sentripetal track.
The place is small for a museum, but turned out that there are a lot of props inside. Nice place to learn physics.
Nice getaway for the kids as it's a educational science center, ready to ignite the spark of curiosity for your young ones towards science and technology.
It is a cheap, easy, nice place for childrens to learn about fun and exciting science experiments.
